 The same region of the hindbrain was then imaged via serial section electron
 microscopy (EM).
 Analysis of the calcium data identified 22 integrator neurons, defined
 by neural activities that were highly correlated with eye position.
 The same neurons were located in the EM dataset, and their neurites were
 completely reconstructed within the confines of the imaged volume.
 
